# ==========================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

## 5. Mandatory Remote Repository Provisioning (The Parity Rule)

**This is a hard rule.** A local `git init` and remote `git remote add origin` without first creating the repository on GitHub is a silent failure — the repo appears healthy locally but has zero remote parity. This is exactly the failure mode that caused `T1-vrvish-profile` to be invisible on GitHub for weeks.

**The Rule:**  
When any agent scaffolds a new platform (Level 5 App) or repository for the first time, it MUST provision the remote GitHub repository **before** the first `git push`. Agents have full authority to do this autonomously using the `GITHUB_PAT` stored in `.env`.

### The Canonical PowerShell Command:
```powershell
$body = '{"name":"REPO_NAME","private":true}'
Invoke-RestMethod -Method POST `
  -Uri "https://api.github.com/user/repos" `
  -Headers @{
    "Authorization"  = "Bearer $env:GITHUB_PAT"
    "Accept"         = "application/vnd.github+json"
    "X-GitHub-Api-Version" = "2022-11-28"
  } `
  -Body $body `
  -ContentType "application/json"
```

Replace `REPO_NAME` with the standard `T1-vrvish-*` or `T4-*` taxonomy name.  
If the API returns `{"message":"Not Found"}`, the PAT lacks `repo` scope — escalate to Commander J.

**After provisioning:** set the remote and push:
```powershell
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/vrvish/REPO_NAME.git
git push -u origin main
```

> [!CAUTION]
> Never assume a remote repo exists. Always verify with `git push -u origin main` *after* explicit API provisioning. If it fails with `repository not found`, run the provisioning step above immediately.